cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about unsupervised neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses neural networks, which suggests that it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Learning). Additionally, the paper compares the performance of different systems, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses sub-character level information, which could potentially involve computer vision techniques, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
